CONTEXT.md calls ToolChoice "the existing exemplar of the value-object pattern the others now follow" — yet ToolChoice is the ONLY tool value object WITHOUT a unified to($fmt) dispatch. Tool->to($fmt), ToolResult->to($fmt) and ToolCall->to_* all gained the tag-keyed dispatch; ToolChoice still exposes only per-format to_openai/to_anthropic/to_perplexity/to_gemini/to_responses. Add ToolChoice->to($fmt) (and document a canonical from form) so all four value objects share one dispatch shape keyed by tool_wire_format. Pure consistency/symmetry, no behaviour change at call sites that already pick the right to_*.
